  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. This package is bound to project requirements documented in the design history file (DHF-NCS-2024-001) and the associated V&V plan (VVP-NCS-2024-003); structured requirement traceability is maintained in the project's requirements management system.",
