    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw, ASTM F1717 compression-bending) is accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged: ASTM F1717 specifies a single standardized test configuration, and the COU is explicitly limited to this configuration, making additional test conditions impracticable and unnecessary. All three QoIs satisfy both quantitative acceptance criteria (< 10% percent difference; E/uval < 1.96). The overall evidence package, including inter-laboratory reproducibility across N=11 specimens, provides sufficient confidence to support regulatory submission. Project requirements traceability is maintained in DHF-NCS-2024-001 and VVP-NCS-2024-003.",
